          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Follow the ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cold-process-soap-method",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "techniqueLink",
                "attrs": {
                  "techniqueSlug": "cold-process-soap-method"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " technique. Melt coconut oil, then combine with castor, olive, and argan oils. Prepare the lye solution by adding sodium hydroxide carefully to the distilled water. Cool both to 40 to 45 degrees Celsius.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Add lye solution to oils and stick-blend to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "trace",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "trace"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Castor oil can accelerate trace, so alternate stick blending with hand stirring and watch the texture. Pour into the mould at light trace, insulate, and leave for 48 hours. Unmould and cure for 4 to 6 weeks. The bar will be firm and lather well once fully cured.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Storage and shelf life"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cured bars keep for 2 years. Store unwrapped on a slatted rack between uses to dry out fully. A dry bar lasts far longer in the shower than one that sits in pooled water. Discard if the bar becomes rancid or shows discolouration.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
